    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Fuel and High-pressure Oil Systems
        - Removal - Fuel Filter Header Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Fuel Filter Header Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f3350007175" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK11/K11002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"/>
            <caption>Fuel filter header</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 75 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 oil filler tube support nut (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 sensor harness retaining nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel outlet fitting (return to tank)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel pump outlet tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water In Fuel (WIF) sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 sensor harness retaining nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel heater (optional)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel pump inlet tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet fitting (from tank)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Priming pump assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not smoke and keep fuel away from flames and sparks.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0707" count="1">Open water drain valve and drain fuel into a correct container clearly marked
                DIESEL FUEL.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the fuel inlet and return lines.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_399.xml" xrefid="s1602">oil filler tube</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s1602"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the WIF sensor, fuel heater, and EFP sensor harness connectors.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen coupling nuts on ends of low-pressure fuel pump inlet tube assembly and remove inlet
                tube assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen coupling nuts on ends of low-pressure fuel pump outlet tube assembly and remove
                outlet tube assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard 3/8 tube sleeves from ends of low-pressure fuel pump inlet and outlet
                tube assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cover openings to fuel filter header and low-pressure fuel pump to prevent dirt entry.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M8 nuts and one M6 x 16 bolt holding the oil filler tube support to the fuel
                filter header.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M10 nut holding sensor harness to intake manifold stud bolt under the fuel filter
                header (Item 3).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M8 nut holding sensor harness to the fuel filter header stud bolt. Remove flat washer
                under the sensor harness retainer.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three M8 x 75 stud bolts and one M8 x 75 bolt holding the fuel filter header to the
                intake manifold and remove the fuel filter header.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the irregular molded gasket from between the fuel filter header and
                intake manifold.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
